/-!
# The Marcinkiewicz-Zygmund inequality

This file proves the Marcinkiewicz-Zygmund inequality.

The Marcinkiewicz-Zygmund inequality states that, if `XвӮҒ, ... XвӮҗ вҲҲ L^p` are independent random
variables of mean zero valued in some inner product space, then the `L^p`-norm of `XвӮҒ + ... + XвӮҗ` is
at most `CвӮҡ` times the `L^(p/2)`-norm of `|XвӮҒ|ВІ + ... + |XвӮҗ|ВІ`, where `CвӮҡ` is a constant depending
on `p` alone.

## Notation

Throughout this file, `A ^^ n` denotes `A Г— ... Г— A` (with `n` factors). Formally, this is
`Fintype.piFinset fun _ : Fin n вҶҰ A`.

## TODO

We currently only prove the inequality for `p = 2 * m` an even natural number. The general `p` case
can be obtained from this specific one by nesting of Lp norms.
-/

